Control of phase separation by pH
In the following, we discuss how the pH controls both chemical and phase equilibrium in our system. We start by discussing the chemical equilibrium conditions (Eq. 11) in terms of newly defined composition variables and thermodynamic fields. After discussing the chemical equilibrium conditions in terms of the pH and the newly defined fields, we provide the conditions for phase equilibrium for a system described by the corresponding thermodynamic potential defined by Eq. 16. We end the section by showing a construction of the coexisting phases for a given choice of parameters.
